    <description>The Solar-Wind (SOW) Instrument on Sakigake (a.k.a. MS-T5) employed a Faraday cup to measure the bulk velocity, density, and temperature of solar-wind ions. This conventional cup, mounted flush with the outer skin of the spacecraft, consisted of four grids and an ion collector. The instrument could detect particles with enegies betwee 0 and 1.5kV. SOW had an adjustable maximum voltage and several operating modes, such as automatic voltage change for every spin, automatic fine voltage sweep between two voltages, etc. The sensor was not sensitive to the solar-wind stream beyond an angle of attack of +/- 60deg.</description>
